{\par \b Syntax:}\par taylor(Expr,[Var=Value],[Order])\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the Taylor series expansion of an expression at a point or at infinity (by default, at x=0 and with relative order=5).\par
{\par \b Example:}\par taylor(sin(x)/x,x=0) returns 1-(1/6)*x^2+(1/120)*x^4+x^6*order_size(x)\par }